Students who are expected to join institutions of higher learning from May have been invited to a mentorship forum. Kenya Universities and Colleges Placement Service (KUCCPS) will hold the forum at Kangaru School in Embu County. "KUCCPS invites all Form Four leavers to a career guidance and mentorship forum on Saturday, January 21, 2023," a tweet reads. The students will get an opportunity to interact with several professionals who will guide them in making career choices This is even as the Ministry of Education is expected to release its results anytime. "The topics will include advice from professionals, the KUCCPS application process and mentorship," the tweet reads.